quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  72,1,"Say, (O Prophet), it was revealed to me that a band of jinn attentively listened to (the recitation of the Qur'an) and then (went back to their people) and said:",footnotes:182336:1
  72,2,"“We have indeed heard a wonderful Qur'an which guides to the Right Way; so we have come to believe in it, and we will not associate aught with Our Lord in His Divinity”;",footnotes:182337:1,footnotes:182338:2
  72,3,"and that “He – exalted be His Majesty – has not taken to Himself either a wife or a son”;",footnotes:182339:1
  72,4,"and that “the foolish among us have been wont to say outrageous things about Allah”;",footnotes:182340:1
  72,5,"and that “we had thought that men and jinn would never speak a lie about Allah”,",footnotes:182341:1
  72,6,"and that “some from among the humans used to seek protection of some among the jinn, and thus they increased the arrogance of the jinn”;",footnotes:182342:1
  72,7,"and that “they thought, even as you thought, that Allah would never raise anyone (as a Messenger)”;",footnotes:182343:1
  72,8,"and that “we tried to pry (the secrets of) the heaven, but we found it full of terrible guards and shooting meteors”;"
  72,9,"and that “we would take up stations in the heaven to try to hear but anyone who now attempts to listen finds a shooting meteor in wait for him”;",footnotes:182344:1
  72,10,"and that “we do not know whether evil is intended for those on the earth, or whether their Lord intends to direct them to the Right Way”;",footnotes:182345:1